Package: frontiermetrics
Type: Package
Title: What the Package Does (Title Case)
Version: 0.0.9
Authors@R: 
    person("Pablo Yair", "Huais", , "pablo.huais@unc.edu.ar", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4062-0779"))
Maintainer: Pablo Yair Huais <pablo.huais@unc.edu.ar>
Description: Provides a toolbox to detect and map high-level patterns of deforestation frontiers. These can be defined as the expansion of woodland loss in a given area with a high level of spatio-temporal detail (Buchadas et al. 2022). We provide functions to calculate, analyze, plot and export deforestation frontier metrics, based on spatio-temporal data provided by Global Forest Watch (Hansen et al. 2013) and a given study area.
